claim.claim-text:
18. An apparatus for polishing surfaces of objects comprising: 
an object transfer station; 
a polishing pad having a polishing surface; 
a first mechanical arm having a first object carrier, said first object carrier being configured to secure a first object to be polished, said first mechanical arm being configured to directly transfer said first object between said object transfer station and said polishing pad using said first object carrier; and 
a second mechanical arm having a second object carrier, said second object carrier being configured to secure a second object to be polished, said second mechanical arm being configured to directly transfer said second object between said object transfer station and said polishing pad using said second object carrier.

24. An apparatus for polishing surfaces of objects comprising: 
an object transfer station; 
a polishing pad having a polishing surface; 
a first object carrier and a second object carrier that are positioned about said polishing surface of said polishing pad to engage said polishing surface of said polishing pad, each of said first and second object carriers being configured to secure an object to be polished; and 
an object transfer mechanism that is configured to directly transfer said objects between said object transfer station and said first and second object carriers.

33. A method of polishing surfaces of objects comprising: 
sequentially receiving a first object and a second object at an object transfer station; 
sequentially transferring said first and second objects from said object transfer station to different locations on a polishing surface of a polishing pad; 
exclusively polishing said first and second objects on said polishing surface of said polishing pad; and 
sequentially outputting said first and second objects that have been polished on said polishing surface of said polishing pad.
